The paper focuses on the use of word embeddings for query expansion in ad hoc information retrieval, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) in computer science. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of word embeddings in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are closely related to IR and could be categorized under cs.CL, cs.LG, and cs.AI. Finally, the paper mentions the use of word embeddings in computer vision (CV), which is less relevant to the main topic but still related to NLP and ML.
